  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>This recipe takes around 5 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[10 min]</span> to prep, so get your oven-proof dish and all your ingredients ready, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Spread your ingredients out over two smaller dishes to avoid overcrowding!</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1650992249539-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1650992249539-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1650992249539-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1650992249539-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Admin10mm-Step-1-1650992249539-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Now let's get started!</strong></p><p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7, then boil a kettle</p><p>Trim, then chop the <strong>green beans</strong> in half</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped green beans</strong> to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (or deep baking tray) with a drizzle of<strong> vegetable oil </strong>and put the tray in the oven for an initial 10 min</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650992308053-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650992308053-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650992308053-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650992308053-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1650992308053-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>basmati rice </strong>to a separate <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> with 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml] </span><strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Cover tightly with<strong> tin foil </strong>and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650992311422-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1650992311422-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
